		}
		{
			description: [
				"Each animal and human being can now bleed. This is an effect that deals damage similar to poison and can be removed using a new item: Bandages. The chance of bleeding is lower the more pieces of armor you have."
				""
				"Bleeding is caused by many different sources such as receiving sword damage, being bitten by a spider, or by touching a cactus..."
				""
				"It is important to keep bandages with you at all times because bleeding becomes more deadly as the game progresses!"
				"{image:majruszsdifficulty:textures/mob_effect/bleeding.png width:30 height:30 align:1}"
			]
			icon: {
				Count: 1
				id: "kubejs:bleed"
				tag: { }
			}
			id: "04CC7C1C1BFE864D"
			rewards: [{
				id: "7B08A97B81394C0F"
				item: "majruszsdifficulty:bandage"
				type: "item"
			}]
			tasks: [{
				id: "344ADACFCEB0D8A7"
				title: "Bleeding"
				type: "checkmark"
			}]
			x: 16.0d
			y: 0.0d
		}
		{
			description: ["The core of the mod is its mechanics, which add new ways to attack and defend. These are intended to supplement the vanilla combat system, and make new playstyles viable. If you aren't sure how to get started, a patchouli guidebook is available, crafted with a book and gold sword."]
			icon: {
				Count: 1b
				ForgeCaps: {
					"dungeons_libraries:built_in_enchantments": { }
				}
				id: "cnb:cinder_sword"
				tag: {
					Damage: 0
				}
			}
			id: "375994C478ED20DF"
			rewards: [{
				id: "730676DC6373DBB9"
				item: {
					Count: 1
					id: "patchouli:guide_book"
					tag: {
						"patchouli:book": "parrying:book"
					}
				}
				type: "item"
			}]
			size: 1.0d
			tasks: [{
				id: "143C73DD83BE9F6C"
				type: "checkmark"
			}]
			title: "Combat Mechanics"
			x: 16.0d
			y: 1.5d
		}
		{
			description: ["Parrying is a relatively simple mechanic. When you are hit with a melee attack, if you are swinging a weapon the attack will be deflected. A \"weapon\" in this case is any item with an attack damage value, eg a sword or pickaxe. To parry, you must be aiming at the attacker. Parrying is easier the higher the attack recharge meter is. A successful parry reduces the defense meter."]
			icon: "kubejs:parry"
			id: "0C2E1DD15D80D4F7"
			tasks: [{
				id: "4F3C6115E95635BD"
				title: "Parrying"
				type: "checkmark"
			}]
			x: 17.0d
			y: 0.0d
		}
		{
			description: ["Dual Wielding allows you to use a weapon from your offhand. Parry This! uses a unique implementation of dual wield. Instead of using right click to trigger an offhand attack, you will alternate between your main and off hands by attacking normally. Dual wielding grants a small boost in attack speed, as well as a penalty for using weapons with differing speeds. Some weapons are marked as \"two handed\", and cannot be used for dual wielding."]
			icon: "kubejs:dualwield"
			id: "4E816C3883966AE9"
			tasks: [{
				id: "71F82111DCCF8E2E"
				title: "Dual Wielding"
				type: "checkmark"
			}]
			x: 17.0d
			y: -1.0d
		}
		{
			description: ["Backstab is a powerful special attack that can be performed by attacking a target from behind. It's hard to hit, but if you get your aim right, you can deal 300% damage to your target. Combined with vanilla stealth mechanics, such as sneaking and invisibility, a rouge or ninja playstyle becomes practical. In pvp, backstabs are practically impossible if your enemy knows you are coming, so use stealth to your advantage. Backstab works with both melee and ranged attacks, making sniping possible as well. Backstab only affects targets with 20 max health or less by default."]
			icon: "kubejs:backstab"
			id: "5005C51CA1B68CC3"
			tasks: [{
				id: "77A86EE482E71220"
				title: "Backstab"
				type: "checkmark"
			}]
			x: 17.0d
			y: -3.0d
		}
		{
			description: ["Dodge is a movement ability, similar to sprinting. By holding alt (configurable) and tapping A, S, or D (or whatever keys your movement is bound to) you can leap left, backwards, or right, respectively. This ability has a short, invisible cooldown. Knockback resistance has an adverse effect on dodging, reducing its power. Thus, wearing Netherite armor will make dodging somewhat less effective. Additionally, you must be touching the ground to dodge, so it may not always be effective in pvp due to the large amount of jumping. The distance you dodge can be improved through the jump boost effect. Each level of jump boost adds roughly one block of dodge distance."]
			icon: "kubejs:dodge"
			id: "14F6CBFA581F6A50"
			tasks: [{
				id: "5E2C34784B3F897E"
				title: "Dodge"
				type: "checkmark"
			}]
			x: 16.0d
			y: -3.0d
		}
		{
			description: ["Certain weapons have a new attribute called \"armor penetration\". This attribute specifies a percentage of the weapon's damage that ignores armor. So if your weapon has 35% armor penetration, 35% of the weapon's damage will ignore armor. All bludgeoning weapons possess armor penetration to varying degrees."]
			icon: "kubejs:armorpen"
			id: "7BD97790AFE589EC"
