				timer: 0L
				title: "Speak to the Hedge-Witch Maren"
				to_observe: "minecraft:witch"
				type: "observation"
			}]
			title: "Maren the Hedge-Witch"
			x: 33.0d
			y: -11.0d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["5300718DDDE89FD4"]
			description: [
				"You've heard Maren's offer. There is nothing stopping you from walking away."
				""
				"&o&8The curse is real — you can feel it sitting in your chest like a cold stone. But Maren used you without permission. She bound your name to a ritual she had no right to perform, and now she expects your cooperation as if that debt runs the other way.&r&r"
				""
				"You will find another way."
				""
				"&4The forest does not care about your principles. The corruption is spreading. And the curse will not wait."
			]
			hide_until_deps_complete: true
			hide_until_deps_visible: true
			icon: "minecraft:barrier"
			id: "76DBD0698BE11CF4"
			rewards: [{
				id: "60C80A4EC6DB1549"
				type: "xp"
				xp: 10
			}]
			subtitle: "&4Incompatible with \"Help Maren\"&r"
			tasks: [{
				id: "43CF8D282378903D"
				title: "Refuse the Witch's Terms"
				type: "checkmark"
			}]
			title: "Refuse Maren"
			x: 34.5d
			y: -9.5d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["76DBD0698BE11CF4"]
			description: [
				"Without Maren's guidance, you have only one option: find the corrupted spirit yourself and destroy it before it destroys you."
				""
				"&o&8The curse feeds on inaction. Every hour you spend not moving, you can feel it tightening — a slow numbness creeping from your fingers upward. You've lost smell. You're losing colour. Soon, you won't feel the cold.&r&r"
				""
				"You need to understand what you're facing. The forest holds traces of the spirit's path — &4blackened bark&r, &5withered flowers&r, &0soil that crumbles to ash&r. Follow the damage and you'll find the source."
				""
				"Maren called it a &4corrupted nature spirit&r. That means it was once something else. Something that remembers being alive."
			]
			hide_until_deps_complete: true
			hide_until_deps_visible: true
			icon: "minecraft:charcoal"
			id: "549BD266B80D0E30"
			rewards: [{
				id: "49AD69668C185D39"
				type: "xp"
				xp: 20
			}]
			tasks: [
				{
					count: 16L
					id: "7624BFB393E3B82A"
					item: "minecraft:charcoal"
					title: "Collect ash-bark from corrupted trees"
					type: "item"
				}
				{
					consume_items: true
					count: 8L
					id: "60BCEA4DE66DBBB2"
					item: "minecraft:dead_bush"
					title: "Gather withered remnants"
					type: "item"
				}
			]
			title: "Track the Corruption Alone"
			x: 36.0d
			y: -9.5d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["549BD266B80D0E30"]
			description: [
				"The trail leads you to a place the map shows as empty — a hollow in the forest floor ringed by dead oaks, their roots knotted together overhead into something that resembles a ribcage."
				""
				"&4The spirit is here.&r"
				""
				"&o&8It has no body, not exactly. It moves between the trees, a rippling wrongness in the air — like heat haze, but cold. You can feel the curse responding to it, pulling at you like a tide. The spirit recognises its own mark.&r&r"
				""
				"You have no ritual. No protection. No binding components."
				""
				"&4You have a weapon and a reason. That will have to be enough."
				""
				"&o&8Maren, watching from somewhere in the tree line, says nothing. She will not help you. She's curious, you realise. She wants to see what happens when someone does this the hard way.&r&r"
			]
			hide_until_deps_complete: true
			hide_until_deps_visible: true
			icon: {
				Count: 1
				id: "ftbquests:custom_icon"
				tag: {
					Icon: "minecraft:textures/block/purple_terracotta.png"
				}
