			y: -5.0d
		}
		{
			description: [
				"You drop into a mineshaft — a routine descent, torches already placed by whoever dug here before you."
				""
				"But thirty blocks down, the wooden supports stop. The tunnel walls change: no longer rough-hewn dirt, but &6dressed stone&r, carved with a precision no modern miner could match."
				""
				"&o&8Someone else was here first. Long before the mineshaft. Long before anyone living can remember. The stonework is immaculate — each block fitted without mortar, smooth as glass. Geometric symbols run along the ceiling in a repeating pattern, worn but still legible to someone who knows what to look for.&r&r"
				""
				"You don't know what to look for. But you know this didn't come from nothing."
				""
				"You keep descending."
			]
			icon: {
				Count: 1
				id: "minecraft:iron_pickaxe"
				tag: {
					Damage: 0
				}
			}
			id: "35FED99D71DA1A18"
			rewards: [{
				id: "421F1719893E197A"
				type: "xp"
				xp: 20
			}]
			tasks: [{
				id: "21A390863990C88A"
				structure: "minecraft:mineshaft"
				title: "Descend into the Mineshaft"
				type: "structure"
			}]
			title: "Something Older Beneath"
			x: 30.0d
			y: -3.0d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["35FED99D71DA1A18"]
			description: [
				"At the base of the shaft, past a collapsed barricade, you find what the mineshaft was unknowingly built on top of:"
				""
				"&6A dwarven settlement.&r"
				""
				"&o&8Not a ruin — or not entirely. The buildings are intact. The streets are swept. The forges are cold but their tools are left neatly on their hooks, as if the smiths stepped away for lunch and simply never came back. There are no bodies. No signs of violence. Just absence.&r&r"
				""
				"A notice board near the settlement's entrance still holds a single posting, the words pressed deep into a copper plate:"
				""
				"&6&o\"BY ORDER OF THE FORGE-MASTERS: All hands to the Deep Works. Bring nothing. Leave nothing. The Vein must be sealed.\"&r&r"
				""
				"&o&8It is not dated. The dwarves did not track time the way surface-folk do.&r&r"
			]
			hide_until_deps_complete: true
			hide_until_deps_visible: true
			icon: "minecraft:copper_ingot"
			id: "47DDA9FE7F251F36"
			rewards: [
				{
					id: "44112349C32BB6E7"
					type: "xp"
					xp: 30
				}
				{
					count: 16
					id: "4669634357AF0C45"
					item: "minecraft:copper_ingot"
					type: "item"
				}
			]
			tasks: [
				{
					id: "7402F20BFA8D14B8"
					structure: "dungeons_enhanced:mining_settlement"
					title: "Find the Dwarven Settlement"
					type: "structure"
				}
				{
					id: "66243C65EE1A593C"
					observe_type: 0
					timer: 0L
					title: "Read the Forge-Masters' notice board"
					to_observe: "minecraft:smithing_table"
					type: "observation"
				}
			]
			title: "The Empty Settlement"
			x: 31.5d
			y: -3.0d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["47DDA9FE7F251F36"]
			description: [
				"You search the settlement for clues about where everyone went."
				""
				"The homes are tidy but personal — a child's toy left on a windowsill, a half-knitted sock on a chair, a pot still hanging over a cold hearth. These weren't soldiers following an evacuation order. These were families."
				""
				"&o&8In the settlement's small library you find a journal. Most of it is mundane: supply orders, shift rotations, complaints about the water pressure in the lower forges. But the final entry is different in tone:&r&r"
				""
				"&6&o\"The Vein sang again last night. Thrumvor says it's getting louder. He won't tell us what it's saying. He says we wouldn't want to know. We leave at first bell. The Deep Works await. Ancestors guide our hands.\"&r&r"
				""
				"&o&8The Vein. Every mention of the dwarves' collapse references it — something they found deep underground that sang. Something that required a seal.&r&r"
				""
				"You are going to need supplies before you follow them down."
			]
			hide_until_deps_complete: true
			hide_until_deps_visible: true
			icon: "minecraft:book"
			id: "0A9AB758ADFBDEBA"
			rewards: [{
				id: "19CC37C0D6C2FB60"
				type: "xp"
				xp: 20
			}]
			tasks: [
				{
					consume_items: true
					count: 64L
					id: "610F08DEEC4E01C5"
					item: "minecraft:torch"
					title: "Pack torches for the deep dark"
					type: "item"
				}
				{
					count: 16L
					id: "11B6CBE9D4939FBD"
					item: "minecraft:iron_ingot"
					title: "Carry iron for repairs"
					type: "item"
				}
				{
					id: "508641FE54F5A6A5"
					item: {
						Count: 1
						id: "minecraft:iron_pickaxe"
						tag: {
							Damage: 0
							Enchantments: [{
								id: "minecraft:efficiency"
								lvl: 2s
							}]
						}
					}
					title: "Bring a proper pickaxe"
					type: "item"
				}
			]
			title: "Read the Journal — Prepare to Descend"
			x: 33.0d
			y: -3.0d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["0A9AB758ADFBDEBA"]
			description: [
				"The passage down from the settlement is wide and well-cut — or was. The dwarven lanterns have guttered out over the centuries."
				""
				"&o&8Your torches cast long shadows on walls that grow more elaborate the deeper you go. The geometric patterns have become something richer: scenes. Histories. A whole civilisation illustrated in bas-relief — dwarves founding their first forge, expanding their tunnels, discovering something vast and bright deep in the rock. The Vein, surely. In the early carvings they are celebrating it. Later, they are kneeling before it. Later still, they are running from it.&r&r"
				""
				"The tunnel narrows. You hear something ahead — not the Vein, but something smaller."
				""
				"&2Scuffling. Muttering. The clink of things being handled carelessly.&r"
				""
				"Goblins. Of course there are goblins."
			]
			hide_until_deps_complete: true
			hide_until_deps_visible: true
			icon: {
				Count: 1
				id: "ftbquests:custom_icon"
				tag: {
					Icon: "minecraft:textures/block/deepslate_tiles.png"
				}
			}
			id: "2BFD9A8BD602BB0F"
			rewards: [{
				id: "5B86F9994877B92C"
				type: "xp"
				xp: 25
			}]
			tasks: [{
				id: "5F226816D032E81C"
				observe_type: 5
				timer: 0L
				title: "Encounter the Goblin Scavengers"
				to_observe: "goblintraders:goblin_trader"
				type: "observation"
			}]
			title: "Something in the Dark"
			x: 34.5d
			y: -3.0d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["2BFD9A8BD602BB0F"]
			description: [
				"A small clan of goblin traders has made camp in an alcove, surrounded by dwarven objects they clearly have no idea how to use."
				""
				"One of them — older, missing an ear, wearing what appears to be a dwarven forge-master's chain as a belt — notices you and immediately begins bargaining."
				""
				"&2&o\"Shiny things! Many shiny things! We found them here, all left behind, nobody wants them! You want? You trade?\"&r&r"
				""
				"&o&8Among the clutter of dwarven tools and ornaments, something catches your eye: a &6small iron medallion&r, stamped with the same symbol above the settlement entrance. The Forge-Masters' seal. It shouldn't be here — it should be with the Forge-Masters. Wherever they went.&r&r"
				""
				"The goblin follows your gaze and clutches it defensively."
				""
				"&2&o\"That one? That one is &nspecial&r&2&o. Very expensive.\"&r&r"
			]
			hide_until_deps_complete: true
			hide_until_deps_visible: true
			icon: "goblintraders:goblin_trader_spawn_egg"
			id: "24E14180599B65BF"
			rewards: [
				{
					id: "5B074D5B0A6FC116"
					type: "xp"
					xp: 20
				}
				{
					count: 8
					id: "727F1AD7318001F1"
					item: "minecraft:gold_nugget"
					type: "item"
				}
			]
			tasks: [
				{
					consume_items: true
					count: 10L
					id: "30E00F73BE8F1EFA"
					item: "minecraft:gold_ingot"
					title: "Pay the goblin's price"
					type: "item"
				}
				{
					count: 32L
					id: "4F307378F6008DB8"
					item: "minecraft:iron_nugget"
					title: "Collect the Forge-Master's medallion"
					type: "item"
				}
			]
			title: "Trade with the Goblin"
			x: 36.0d
			y: -3.0d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["24E14180599B65BF"]
			description: [
				"Medallion in hand, you press deeper."
				""
				"The passage eventually opens into a vast underground chamber — the &6Deep Works.&r"
				""
				"&o&8The scale is staggering. Forge-towers rise from the cavern floor to the distant ceiling, connected by walkways and ramps. Every surface is covered in carved symbols, but here they are inlaid with dark metal, and they still faintly &4glow&r. At the chamber's far end, a great sealed door — easily fifteen metres tall — bears the Forge-Masters' emblem enlarged a hundredfold.&r&r"
				""
				"And in front of it, arranged in a semicircle, are the dwarves."
				""
				"&o&8They are not moving. Not dead, not exactly — preserved in a state between rest and stone. Their faces are peaceful. Each one faces the door. Each one holds a tool. They finished the job. They sealed The Vein. And then they stayed to make sure it held.&r&r"
				""
				"&4The door hums. The Vein, behind it, is still singing."
			]
			hide_until_deps_complete: true
			hide_until_deps_visible: true
			icon: {
				Count: 1
				id: "ftbquests:custom_icon"
				tag: {
					Icon: "minecraft:textures/block/deepslate_bricks.png"
				}
			}
			id: "35B611772CD81F5E"
			rewards: [
				{
					id: "57D5DE0EF31C83E5"
					type: "xp"
					xp: 60
				}
				{
					count: 8
					id: "1D02990E3F2D853C"
					item: "minecraft:deepslate_iron_ore"
					type: "item"
				}
			]
			tasks: [
				{
					id: "53A0B16C58AED063"
					structure: "when_dungeons_arise:infested_temple"
					title: "Find the Deep Works"
					type: "structure"
				}
				{
					entity: "minecraft:silverfish"
					id: "3C0FC403464A5617"
					title: "Clear the infested outer chambers"
					type: "kill"
					value: 20L
				}
				{
					entity: "minecraft:cave_spider"
					id: "3B56BB644C301EA4"
					title: "Cleanse the nesting passages"
					type: "kill"
					value: 15L
				}
			]
			title: "The Deep Works"
			x: 37.5d
			y: -3.0d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["35B611772CD81F5E"]
			description: [
				"You stand before the sealed door for a long time."
				""
				"&o&8The medallion in your hand grows warm. The door's emblem and the medallion's stamp are identical — and you realise the medallion is not a record of ownership. It is a key.&r&r"
				""
				"The Forge-Master who carried it must have dropped it on the way down. Or left it deliberately."
				""
				"&4The Vein behind the door is louder now that you're close. Not quite a sound — more like a pressure in the chest. A sense that something on the other side knows you're there, and is very, very pleased you've arrived.&r&r"
				""
				"You have two choices:"
				""
				"&6Use the medallion to open the door — and face whatever The Vein actually is.&r"
				""
				"&8Or leave it. Walk back up. Let the dwarves keep their vigil undisturbed.&r"
			]
			hide_until_deps_complete: true
			hide_until_deps_visible: true
			icon: "minecraft:iron_ingot"
			id: "1D21F8BF8535A52C"
			rewards: [{
				id: "1542D349BB433626"
				type: "xp"
				xp: 30
			}]
			subtitle: "&4Incompatible with \"Leave the door sealed\"&r"
			tasks: [{
				id: "188FFDD42D0F1AA6"
				title: "Use the Key"
				type: "checkmark"
			}]
			title: "Open the Sealed Door"
			x: 39.0d
			y: -4.0d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["35B611772CD81F5E"]
			description: [
				"You look at the sleeping dwarves. You look at the door."
				""
				"&8You place the medallion on the ground between two of the Forge-Masters.&r"
				""
				"&o&8It doesn't belong to you. It didn't belong to the goblin who had it. It belongs here, with the people who made it, doing the job they built it to do.&r&r"
				""
				"You turn around and begin the long climb back to the surface."
				""
				"&o&8Behind you, the hum changes pitch — almost imperceptibly. The Vein goes a little quieter.&r&r"
				""
				"You don't look back."
			]
			hide_until_deps_complete: true
			hide_until_deps_visible: true
			icon: "minecraft:stone_bricks"
			id: "71246B33DA11E8D9"
			rewards: [
				{
					id: "71352169716FADD9"
					type: "xp"
					xp: 80
				}
				{
					count: 12
					id: "66E251CB9FA506FF"
					item: "minecraft:iron_ingot"
					type: "item"
				}
				{
					id: "7CB1C7F8ABBE5E70"
					item: {
						Count: 1
						id: "minecraft:enchanted_book"
						tag: {
							StoredEnchantments: [{
								id: "minecraft:mending"
								lvl: 1s
							}]
						}
					}
					type: "item"
				}
			]
			subtitle: "&4Incompatible with \"Open the Sealed Door\"&r"
			tasks: [{
				id: "5DBEA4D1A9BFBF26"
				title: "Leave the Door Sealed"
				type: "checkmark"
			}]
			title: "Leave the door sealed"
			x: 39.0d
			y: -2.0d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["1D21F8BF8535A52C"]
			description: [
				"The door does not open with a groan or a crash. It dissolves — the stone pulling itself apart in perfect silence, each block receding into the wall as if it was always meant to be there."
				""
				"&o&8Beyond it is not a chamber. It is a &4vein of crystal&r — a seam running through the rock from floor to ceiling, descending at an angle into the earth for as far as your torch can illuminate. The crystals are the colour of deep amber, pulsing with a slow rhythmic light. Like breathing.&r&r"
				""
				"&4The Vein is alive.&r"
				""
				"&o&8It is not malevolent. Not welcoming. Simply present — enormous and ancient and indifferent in the way mountains are indifferent. But it notices you. A gentle pressure. A warmth. A sense of being observed by something that has no concept of time or danger or consequence.&r&r"
				""
				"You think you understand now why the dwarves stayed."
				""
				"You think you understand why the Forge-Masters sealed it."
				""
				"&4You are not sure those two things are compatible."
			]
			hide_until_deps_complete: true
			hide_until_deps_visible: true
			icon: "minecraft:amethyst_shard"
			id: "56742958BEAAE440"
			rewards: [{
				id: "244511AB907839DD"
				type: "xp"
				xp: 30
			}]
			tasks: [{
				elapsedTime: 240L
				id: "7AFC870FD1528DCA"
				title: "Stand before the Vein in silence"
				type: "questsadditions:time"
			}]
			title: "What the Dwarves Found"
			x: 40.5d
			y: -4.0d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["56742958BEAAE440"]
			description: [
				"The longer you stand in the Vein's presence, the more you understand."
				""
				"&o&8Not in words — the Vein doesn't think in words. But in impressions. You see the dwarves finding it, millennia ago, and the joy of it. You see them building their civilisation around its warmth. You see the moment, generations later, when they realised the warmth was &4changing&r — pulling at them, drawing them inward, making it harder and harder to remember the surface.&r&r"
				""
				"&4The Vein was not trying to harm them. It simply wanted company.&r"
				""
				"&o&8But the Forge-Masters understood: something that cannot comprehend harm is still capable of causing it. So they built the seal. They stayed to hold it. And they sent the medallion away with a courier who never arrived.&r&r"
				""
				"You pry a single fragment from the vein wall. The crystal sings against your palm — a clear, high note, satisfied."
				""
				"The door reseals behind you as you leave."
				""
				"&o&8The dwarves are still at their posts. You think — you aren't certain — that one of them is smiling now.&r&r"
			]
			hide_until_deps_complete: true
			hide_until_deps_visible: true
			icon: "minecraft:amethyst_block"
			id: "35EDEA3061D1ADAC"
			rewards: [
				{
					id: "712DD6D3C8D1A479"
					type: "xp"
					xp: 150
				}
				{
					id: "7621626C508A2D86"
					item: {
						Count: 1
						id: "ftbquests:lootcrate"
						tag: {
							type: "dungeon_artifact_crate"
						}
					}
					type: "item"
				}
				{
					count: 4
					id: "1724ADB76091663D"
					item: "minecraft:amethyst_shard"
					type: "item"
				}
				{
					id: "7C9E88144EEEFD23"
					item: {
						Count: 1
						id: "minecraft:enchanted_book"
						tag: {
							StoredEnchantments: [{
								id: "minecraft:fortune"
								lvl: 3s
							}]
						}
					}
					type: "item"
				}
			]
			tasks: [
				{
					consume_items: true
					id: "0EFB7EBF968056A8"
					item: "minecraft:amethyst_shard"
					title: "Take a fragment of the Vein"
					type: "item"
				}
				{
					entity: "minecraft:warden"
					id: "56DD15171EA60DBC"
					title: "Silence the Vein's guardian"
					type: "kill"
					value: 1L
				}
